    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-06-08T04:06:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-06-08T04:06:00-05:00" n="582"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d582">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_MHF1">Matthews</persName> files, lot 53 D 413:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief, United Nations Command (<persName
                            corresp="#p_CGMW1" type="from">Clark</persName>) to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Joint Chiefs of Staff</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-06-08T18:06:00+09:00"
                            >June 8, 1953—6:06 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>C 62910. Ref: A. CX 62890.<note n="1" xml:id="d582fn1">Dated June 7, <ref
                            target="frus1952-54v15p1#pg_1149">p. 1149</ref>.</note> B. Ltr, AGJ
                    370.2 (4 May 53) CJ–P, Hq Far East Comd, 22 May 53, subj: Revised Outline Plan
                        <gloss target="#t_EVERREADY1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">EverReady</hi>
                    </gloss>.<note n="2" xml:id="d582fn2">Letter not printed (Department of Defense
                        files); for Outline Plan <gloss target="#t_EVERREADY1">Everready</gloss>,
                        May 4, see <ref target="frus1952-54v15p1#pg_965">p. 965</ref>.</note> This
                    msg in 2 parts.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Part I.</hi>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>
                        <hi rend="italic">a</hi>.</label>
                    <item>In order to be prepared for the remote possibility that the <gloss
                            target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> govt may take unilateral action due to curr
                        armistice developments, I have reviewed existing directives in light of the
                        curr sit (ref A) and have issued the instructions contained in part
                        II.</item>
                    <label>
                        <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.</label>
                    <item>All component comdrs are fully alert to the sit and their aprop plans have
                        been revised.</item>
                    <label>
                        <hi rend="italic">c</hi>.</label>
                    <item>These instructions to my component comdrs are being forwarded to you by
                        wire, in order that you will have them aval for ready ref in the remote case
                        it becomes nec to implement any portion of these instructions.</item>
                </list>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Part II</hi>
                </p>
                <p>To: Commanding Gen, United States Army Forces, Far East; Commander Naval Forces,
                    Far East; Commanding Gen, Far East Air Forces.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Eff date: The provisions of this ltr are eff for planning purposes upon
                        receipt and for execution <hi rend="italic">only</hi> upon my personal
                        order.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>References: <pb facs="0035" n="1153" xml:id="pg_1153"/>
                        <list>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">a</hi>.</label>
                            <item>Ltr, AG 312.1 (29 Dec 52) JSPOG, Hq Far East Comd, 29 Dec 1952,
                                subj: Ltr of instructions.<note n="3" xml:id="d582fn3">Not
                                    found.</note>
                            </item>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.</label>
                            <item>Eight Army outline plan “<gloss target="#t_EVERREADY1">Ever
                                    Ready</gloss>”, 4 May 1953.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Assumptions: <list>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">a</hi>.</label>
                            <item>That the <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> is committed to
                                acceptance of curr proposed armistice agreements.</item>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.</label>
                            <item>That the <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> will assume
                                responsibility to assure compliance with provisions of such
                                armistice agreements.</item>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">c</hi>.</label>
                            <item>That the present <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> govt will be
                                reluctant to acpt the terms of the armistice and this reluctance may
                                produce any one of the folg conditions: <list>
                                    <label>(1)</label>
                                    <item>
                                        <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> trps, while not overtly
                                        hostile, are not responsive to <gloss target="#t_UNC1"
                                            >UNC</gloss> directives. (Condition A).</item>
                                    <label>(2)</label>
                                    <item>
                                        <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> govt and mil units
                                        proceed along an independent course of action. (Condition
                                        B).</item>
                                    <label>(3)</label>
                                    <item>
                                        <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> govt, mil units or
                                        people are overtly hostile to <gloss target="#t_UNC1"
                                            >UNC</gloss> trps. (Condition C).</item>
                                </list>
                            </item>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</label>
                            <item>That present favorable relationships between <gloss
                                    target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> forces and the <gloss
                                    target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> Army may decline gradually or
                                suddenly and the conditions described in subparas (1), (2) and (3)
                                above may develop in sequences, or any one of the conditions may be
                                precipitated on short notice. (<hi rend="italic">Note:</hi> There is
                                currently no accepted evaluated intelligence which indicates that
                                such conditions will dev.)</item>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">e</hi>.</label>
                            <item>In the event that the present <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss>
                                govt cannot be forced to acpt the armistice terms, an amenable
                                    <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> govt, with a reasonable
                                capability of controlling and maj elements of the Republic of Korea
                                Armed Forces, the national police, and the pers engaged in log
                                support operations of the <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss>, can
                                be established.</item>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">f</hi>.</label>
                            <item>That if conditions indicated in assumption <hi rend="italic"
                                    >e</hi> above prove not to be factual, the obligations under
                                assumption <hi rend="italic">b</hi> will take second priority, and
                                the <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> will devote its maj effort
                                to actions designed to insure its ability to maintain intact the maj
                                mil elements of the <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss>.</item>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">g</hi>.</label>
                            <item>That, despite an armistice agreement, the Communists may attack at
                                any time.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Plans: <list>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">a</hi>.</label>
                            <item>Be prepared to take such measures as are deemed nec to insure the
                                scty of <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> forces in the event an
                                emerg is created by any action on the part of the Republic of Korea
                                govt.</item>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.</label>
                            <item>Take nec action to insure the integrity of <gloss target="#t_UNC1"
                                    >UNC</gloss> forces.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>Missions: <list>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">a</hi>.</label>
                            <item>Army Forces Far East. <list>
                                    <label>(1)</label>
                                    <item>Continue presently asgd mission.</item>
                                    <pb facs="0036" n="1154" xml:id="pg_1154"/>
                                    <label>(2)</label>
                                    <item>Be prepared to implement Eighth Army outline plan “<gloss
                                            target="#t_EVERREADY1">Ever Ready</gloss>” on my
                                        order.</item>
                                    <label>(3)</label>
                                    <item>Action to establish a <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss>
                                        Mil Govt in the Republic of Korea will not be
                                        undertaken.</item>
                                    <label>(4)</label>
                                    <item>Upon implementation of outline plan “<gloss
                                            target="#t_EVERREADY1">Ever Ready</gloss>”, <gloss
                                            target="#t_KCOMZ1">KCOMZ</gloss> will be attached to
                                        Eighth Army for opnl control.</item>
                                </list>
                            </item>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.</label>
                            <item>Naval Forces, Far East. <list>
                                    <label>(1)</label>
                                    <item>Continue presently asgd missions.</item>
                                    <label>(2)</label>
                                    <item>Support the <gloss target="#t_CGAFFE1">CG AFFE</gloss> as
                                        required in the implementation of outline plan “<gloss
                                            target="#t_EVERREADY1">Ever Ready</gloss>”.</item>
                                </list>
                            </item>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">c</hi>.</label>
                            <item>Far East [Air] Forces. <list>
                                    <label>(1)</label>
                                    <item>Continue presently asgd mission.</item>
                                    <label>(2)</label>
                                    <item>Support the <gloss target="#t_CGAFFE1">CG AFFE</gloss> as
                                        required in the implementation of outline plan “<gloss
                                            target="#t_EVERREADY1">Ever Ready</gloss>”.</item>
                                </list>
                            </item>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</label>
                            <item>For all commanders. When the conditions of outline plan “<gloss
                                    target="#t_EVERREADY1">Ever Ready</gloss>” as listed below are
                                in effect, comdrs will take the folg actions: <list>
                                    <label>(1)</label>
                                    <item>Condition A (passive resistance to <gloss target="#t_UNC1"
                                            >UNC</gloss> leadership and direction). <list>
                                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                                            <item>Intensify intel coverage of all <gloss
                                                  target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> govt and mil
                                                activities.</item>
                                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                                            <item>Maintain scty of all <gloss target="#t_UNC1"
                                                  >UNC</gloss> installations and facilities.</item>
                                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                                            <item>Alert all <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss>
                                                units for emerg action, in accordance with curr
                                                plans.</item>
                                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">d</hi>)</label>
                                            <item>Initiate action to reduce levels of supply for
                                                  <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> forces.</item>
                                        </list>
                                    </item>
                                    <label>(2)</label>
                                    <item>Condition B (overt violation of armistice agreement, but
                                        no maj hostile activity directly toward <gloss
                                            target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> trps). <list>
                                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                                            <item>Remove <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> mil
                                                units and indigenous pers from vital <gloss
                                                  target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> log installations in
                                                Korea.</item>
                                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                                            <item>Close out non-essential log installations in
                                                Korea.</item>
                                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                                            <item>Discontinue air and naval support of <gloss
                                                  target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> forces.</item>
                                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">d</hi>)</label>
                                            <item>Prep to discontinue log support of all <gloss
                                                  target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> mil forces.</item>
                                        </list>
                                    </item>
                                </list>
                            </item>
                            <label>(3)</label>
                            <item>Condition C (maj hostile action directly against <gloss
                                    target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> forces). Be prepared to execute
                                plans to evac Korea on my order.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>6.</label>
                    <item>Copies of these instructions will be furn only to members of your staff on
                        a strict “need to know” basis. In the dissemination of these instructions to
                        subor comdrs you are authorized to make such pertinent extracts as are
                        deemed essential in the execution of your mission. Auth is herewith granted
                        to make extracts of outline plan “<gloss target="#t_EVERREADY1">Ever
                            Ready</gloss>” as are required. Sgd <persName corresp="#p_CGMW1">Mark W.
                            Clark</persName>, Gen United States Army.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
